CAPE TOWN - A wreath laying ceremony to remember Courtney Pieters will take place in Cape Town on Sunday afternoon.The three-year-old from Elsies River was last seen playing in a street near her home over a week ago. Police and community volunteers discovered the body of the little girl in a shallow grave in Epping, in Elsies River on Saturday afternoon.Residents had been banding together to conduct around-the-clock searches. Authorities say they are concerned about the number of young children going missing on the Cape Flats.Police say their crime experts and forensic pathologist have combed through the scene for evidence.eNCA